<br>
-Lures added at lower levels, or resistances on monsters lowered when a wizard is nuking rather than another class.<br>
<br>
-More mana efficiency on nukes, if this is not possible, add new researchable, or looted nukes that have better efficency than our vendor spells. I.E: Wizard NPC's in Permafrost can randomly drop spells in or below their level range. these nukes can either be A. doing more damage than vendor nukes of that level, while being more resistable. or B. doing similar damage to the level's vendor nukes, while having a lower mana cost and similar resistability as vendor nukes. This will allow Wizards to get a more diverse spell book.<br>
<br>
-Lower damage on other classes nukes. if this is not possible, raise the damage on Wizard nukes by about 10%. VI talks about Wizards stepping on Magician territory by having bolts, other classes are stepping on our territory by having nukes that are of a very similar damage or mana efficiency to ours.<br>
<br>
-Make FT items available at lower levels. or add &quot;Caster Disciplines&quot; (this applies to all caster classes other than hybrids) that will regen mana at a very high rate for say, 3 ticks have have a base reuse time of 10 minutes.<br>
<br>
-A mana bonus for Int casters for reaching 255 int, so say that very last point gives you 100 mana, same could be done for wis casters, except hybrids<br>
<br>
-(Many thanks to Grimstaff for this idea) add a few very slow casting highly mana inefficient nukes at various levels. I.E a 300 damage nuke at 20 that costs 350 mana to cast with maybe a 5 second casting time. allowing wizards to do alot of damage in a single blast. and add a few very fast casting mana efficient nukes at various levels that will do less damage than a nuke of the same level, very much like a draught. This can be applied in conjunction with the drop spells in an earlier idea, having some at vendors and some in dungeons. This will allow many underused lower level dungeons and zones to be repopulated with newer characters looking for these new spells.<br>
<br>
-Taunt component on Wizard DDs lowered, this will allow Wizards to nuke a bit more than they do in combat<br>
<br>
-I haven't used a Flappy yet so table is open to ideas for them<br>
<br>
There we have it. the compilation of the most sensible ideas i have read and a couple of my own.<br>
<br>
EDIT: Added last 2 statements. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukilzadikandinsky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KilzadiKandinsky</A> at: 7/17/02 5:11:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uluxum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luxum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 672<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/18/02 4:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> resistances on monsters lowered when a wizard is nuking rather than another class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
