<br>
For every 10 points of int above 100, spells do between 2 and 5 percent additional damage.<br>
<br>
For every 5 points of int above 200, an additional 5 percent damage is done.<br>
<br>
If stamina(it IS the secondary stat for wizards) is used to help our mana regen, provide an adjustment to our mana pool, or both were implemented, then that would also help.<br>
<br>
Add buffs for enchanters that would grant focus-type effects that stack with focus items.  If a haste buff stacks with a haste item, then why not a double focus if we have a buff?<br>
<br>
Put in more focus items that are class specific(or added to existing class specific items), which do more than the general &quot;all classes&quot; focus items.  Wizard specific improved damage focus items that do more than the &quot;up to 20 percent&quot; of existing focus items.  <br>
<br>
An &quot;enhanced&quot; version of invisibility that NOTHING can see thought without having a see invis put on it.  The number of mobs in game that can see invisible as a natural ability is very high in the 35+ game.  You'd figure a wizard would have figured out why, and improved the invisibility spells so whatever lets them naturally see invis would be nullified.<br>
