 PS: I dont even have the fabulous flaming sword yet! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 5461<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/22/02 5:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> Other classes shouldn't have gotten as many nor as potent nukes as they did.  But they have them, so the answer isn't to weaken other classes (just take note other game designers).  It just takes a little minor tweaking of Wizards to make the blasts more noticably superior and effective as they should be.  <br>
<br>
Slightly lower mana cost - this doesn't have to change much, 10% maximum lower mana for blasts only.<br>
Slightly faster blasts - this again doesn't have to be much, but should be done mostly at higher levels.  Between level 29 and 49 the casting times on blasts become absurd, even Verant recognized that (its why we have Draughts in the 50s).  A small shift, lowering by around 5-10% each would make the blasts come in when they need to without a real change in power for Wizards.  It wouldn't make Wizards more POTENT it would make them better designed and distinctive.<br>
Lowering recast times - there's lots of rumors and theories running around about recast times, but the simple fact is we all know that this can be cut down without breaking the game.  Lowering Wizard nuke recast times by half would make chain casting more of a valid option in emergencies.<br>
Lower Aggro - If you nuke faster for less mana, you'll be doing more damage overall with the same bar of mana (this would mean no need for mana regen effects, etc, etc).  However, doing so would get you turned into paste faster, and this would negate the entire advantage.  Lowering aggro slightly for the spells would allow Wizard to distinctly deal thier direct damage in a superior way to other casters.<br>
<br>
What's that, you say, Focus items do all this?  But they do it for ALL classes, not just Wizards.  Wizards SPECIFICALLY need work, just like Mages, Rangers, etc.  Changing all casters uniformly (oh, except for pet classes) doesn't help the individual ones, particularly in terms of balance relative to each other.<br>
<br>
There's other little things, such as the aforementioned low level Lure spells and more AE types at lower levels, but these are the major changes that would really make a difference.<br>
<br>
This is all pretty old stuff, I've posted my whole fix it list a couple times in the past and don't really feel a burning need to do so again.  The point is moot, none of this will happen. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 7/22/02 8:59:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukilzadikandinsky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KilzadiKandinsky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/22/02 8:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> see. now we're actually getting some intelligent posts in class balance forum *Gasp*. more choice in AEs would be nice. but Verant wont do that because it might set us up for better quadding, or AE groups, Druid nukes are almost as good as ours. they can evac, they can port, they can dot, they can sow, buff, regen. now thats absurd, they shouldn't have nukes as powerful as ours. they have similar variety to their nukes. our draughts may be slighter faster casting. but that doesn't balance us. now. lets have some ideas on Flappy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 704<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/28/02 8:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span cl