<br>
Agreed, but they could also give us +5% more damage and -5% mana savings on each spell. I'd be content with that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Slightly faster blasts - this again doesn't have to be much, but should be done mostly at higher levels. Between level 29 and 49 the casting times on blasts become absurd, even Verant recognized that (its why we have Draughts in the 50s). A small shift, lowering by around 5-10% each would make the blasts come in when they need to without a real change in power for Wizards. It wouldn't make Wizards more POTENT it would make them better designed and distinctive.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
There is no reason to drop the cast times on our 29-49 spells. With focus items, you can shave 10% off the cast time, which in most cases fixes the problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lowering recast times - there's lots of rumors and theories running around about recast times, but the simple fact is we all know that this can be cut down without breaking the game. Lowering Wizard nuke recast times by half would make chain casting more of a valid option in emergencies.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You can avoid the network latency which plagues spell gems popping up instantly by using an instant click item right after casting.<br>
Other than that, we really don't have much for recast times, minus our AEs, which won't get touched now.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lower Aggro - If you nuke faster for less mana, you'll be doing more damage overall with the same bar of mana (this would mean no need for mana regen effects, etc, etc).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'm all for this! Except I'd like to see it in a form similar to concussion. Maybe around level 16, a quest spell perhaps, or maybe research...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What's that, you say, Focus items do all this? But they do it for ALL classes, not just Wizards. Wizards SPECIFICALLY need work, just like Mages, Rangers, etc.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
No, they're not for all classes. Ask the rogues and monks about them. They got nuthin with focus items, and that's whos damage we're trying to match (or beat).<br>
Bards can't use them either, and they could probably get the most use out of the of all the classes. Imagine if bards could twist 5 or 6 songs instead the average 3-4. That would be scary! Bards might actually rival some pure classes in abilities.<br>
<br>
I honestly have come to the point where I think we're balanced. A wise man ones said, 'you can tell when classes are balanced, because everybody bitches at about the same frequency.'. <br>
Well, in the past few months people have been bitching at about the same frequency, so I'd say we're either balanced or damn close.<br>
<br>
The real problem with the wizard class is that our presence isn't felt, heard or seen, minus when we get massive critical hits we look like we sit on our ass and do nothing.<br>
It's a flaw with the class, and it's one that needs to be improved a bit. <br>
We need to 'wow' other classes into wanting us, and right now we don't have the tools to do that in the low to mid-level ranges. With AA, we're pretty impressive.<br>
<br>
I could sit here and spout off spells, skills, and items that would give us wow factor, but the point is, Wizards in SOE's eyes are about where they want them, just like most other classes. <br>
They're going to tweak classes here and there as need be, but they aren't going to be making huge sweeping changes because people aren't feeling good about their class.<br>
<br>
Remember, wizards in EQ are part of their vision, not yours or mine.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usnyine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snyine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 1:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> make flappies mana regen group related .... make flappy have additional effect of all the focus items in game but at a lower level .... increase casting time increase damage and reduce mana cost and aggro :P then flappy would rule :P <br>
