<br>
Previously, the flaming sword was an unrealistic avenue due to the high mana cost and the speed at which most mobs die in a grind group. Assuming that some of the changes go live including the reduced mana cost of the sword, then it may be a viable option of adding sdps to wizards. I can honestly say that while attempting to solo with the flaming sword proves humorous to witnesses it's a pain in the ass. I don't care what sort of efficiency I achieve -- You won't find me agro kiting something so that my sword can beat on it. I don't have the patience /shrug.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't mind seeing this line extend down to our lower levels. It wouldn't be hard to imagine a line up of these spells dancing swords, maces, daggers, and the like. It seems like a reasonable way they could add sdps without increasing our effectiveness at soloing. Again, I think some people may really dislike this idea, but from the countless &quot;balance idea!&quot; threads I'd say the community at large is having difficulty focusing on any single solution. Most people are in agreement about the major shortcomings, but not everyone agrees on how to resolve that. I think, in most instances, the suggestions for resolving the issue end up with a lot of unintended fringe benefits, which would result in a major power shift. <br>
<br>
Additionally, I would love to see our less useful spell lines converted into something useful. This includes our O'Kiels and Al'Kabor's lines. People have made scores of suggestions regarding these two lines and ways in which they could be made useful. Right now, that is probably my single largest pet peave and I see balance tweaks as a viable means to kill two birds with one stone. I get a worthless line or two of spells converted into something useful, and I get &quot;balance.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tal<br>
