<br>
GENERAL<br>
-Reduce resistances for Wizard attack spells from level 1-60, not an alleged reduction at level 35+. What resists a cleric would resist a Wizard like it was one color shift lower (whites like blues, etc). <br>
This offsets the lack of Wizard ability to get around resistances (with pets, buffs, etc), and makes the class immediately more attractive to groups - that guy will land his spells. It also makes the Wizard's mana more effective, since the Wizard is a mana hose. <br>
-Reduce resistances further for creatures lower level than the Caster, such as 15 levels at level 30. This would be for all casters, Moss snakes shouldn't shrug off spells from a level 55 Magician or Necro either. <br>
-If not this, then a minimum damage level for Caster Spells against targets below a certain level (like 15 levels under you). <br>
-Change Enstill to have a minimum duration if the creature is undamaged, like mez <br>
-make Paralyzing Earth area effect Root <br>
-Have aggro based on the intellect of the monster. I can see Vox recognizing that Conflag could have done 625 damage when it only did 6, but should a Grizzly Bear? <br>
-Fix the Concussion quest so someone under level 50 has a reasonable shot at doing the quest. This is really an embarrassment.  An alternative is just to make it available for sale or research.<br>
-Make the reagent for Diamondskin a Pearl, not a Peridot. For the effect and level this is absurdly overpriced, it just isn't worth using.<br>
<br>
ATTACK<br>
-Speed casting time by as much as 10% across the board past level 29. 6.3 seconds is unacceptable for a blast, that's longer than gate. Yes, this includes Draught spells, there's no excuse for them to be slower than the equivalent fast spells of other classes (see Scars of Sigil).  <br>
-Lower mana cost for all blasts by 10% or more, resulting in even more efficient spells. Less mana cost = no need for faster mana regeneration for Wizards. <br>
-Shorten recast delay between blasts by 1 second or so. Presently the delay is 2.2 to 2.5 seconds, this would make it 1.2 to 1.5 seconds. This would be limited to only normal blasts without extra effects. <br>
-Increase damage the few levels Wizards are out damaged by other classes in a single blast. There aren't many of these levels, but if it is acceptible for a Druid to do 22 damage at level 5, then it certainly is for Wizards to do 23, and at better mana cost.<br>
<br>
For example, at level 1, Clerics have the most powerful nuke in the game, doing 6 damage at level 1 and capping at 8 damage at level 3.  By comparison, Wizards do at best 4 damage at level 1 and 6 damage at level 3, Magicians and druids do 3-5 damage.  This was defended by Verant claiming that Clerics needed help at lower levels (??)<br>
At level 5, Wizards do 14 damage with their best blast, while Druids do 22 damage, and Clerics do 16 damage with their nukes.  The Druid damage isnt even defended, presumably the concept would be that it only works outdoors, but that is hardly justification for a 50% greater damage, more mana efficient blast.<br>
At level 34, Wizards do 306 damage, while Magicians are doing 319 damage.  The Mage attack is a bolt, which has its own limitations but if that was justification for such a discrepency in damage then EVERY level Mages get a bolt it should be higher than the Wizard blast... and its not. <br>
 <br>
-Add in more blasts per circle of spells. Dipping up to 15 levels for a type of attack is totally unacceptable, every level should have at least 2 types of attack spells.  (suggestions of how to do so follow)<br>
-Add in Lure spells at level 24 and 34 (magic and cold respectively). This is done for two reasons, primarily being that lures ignore the 6+/1.2x resist cap. The other reason is the scattered rare creatures who are immune to magic such as EXG in Solusek A. <br>
-Add in superfast casting low efficiency, lower damage blasts scattered through the levels; something like a 75 point blast at level 20 that costs 100 mana and casts at 1.5-2 seconds. <br>
-Add in HUGE superpower blasts that cast very slowly and take whale loads of mana with a long recast hold time (for example, 250 damage at level 20, but costs 300 mana and takes 6 seconds to cast, with a 1 minute hold time), these would be few in number, perhaps at level 29 and 39 only.<br>
<br>
These two blasts give not only a way to fill in the extra blasts per level called for, but also give Wizards greater utility with what they have. This would make Wizard DD significantly and noticably better to all viewers than other classes... having a bare margin if any with an ability nearly every other class has is not mastery... and its a poor concept for class design.<br>
<br>
-Scatter more AE types through levels so you have each type every other spell circle. That means more options and better progression. <br>
-Change Al'Kabor to have unlimited target maximum, their poor damage and mana efficiency negates the possibility of exploiting this for experience. <br>
-Extend the range of Wizard blasts to 300 instead of 200, so that Wizards clearly have an advantage in attack spells. <br>
-Add a no-damage interrupt spell that cast quickly but is resisted like a stun spell. If it worked, it would stop casting in the creature but not do damage. This would be most useful at higher levels, perhaps at level 34+. <br>
This one is iffy, but would definitely make us more attractive to groups. This would turn casters off more often than not, its something Bards can do at level 28 with Pixie Strike (mes/damage song interrupts spells). <br>
-Fix AE Rain spells to hit with up to 3 waves on each of up to 4 targets. <br>
This would likely require the more powerful AE Rain spells to be lowered in damage. <br>
-The alternative is to raise the level 5-50 AE rain spells to greater power and make them ALL single target spells. Having done so this would require more AE spells scattered where rain was supposed to fill the gap... and it would make Magicians much happier. <br>
-Scale up damage, so each Draught and Lure spell does more than the previous version post 50. <br>
-Move Sunstrike to level 53, add in a new more powerful (1800 pt) blast at level 57.  Too powerful in the old world? Tell that to the guys with all those keen weapons. You ARE level 60, after all, if I go into Crushbone at level 40, I am pretty powerful. <br>
-A possibility is to Remove the cap to damage adders to spells, so that they keep going up until level 60,  This would make Shock of Frost do an astonishing 64 damage at level 60 (ooh, game breaking - Conflag, by comparison would do 680). Why DOES Ice Comet and Rend stop giving more damage at level 50? <br>
-Make AE spells have a Line of Sight from their target, so they will hit things the target can see but the Wizard cannot. Is it an explosion or not?<br>
 <br>
DEFENSE<br>
-Add in a minor skin line below level 16 when Wizards are incredibly vulnerable and die the easiest of any class in the game. level 4 (Malachite (5 silver), 12 pts max protection) and 12 (Turquoise (1 gold), 30 pts max protection)<br>
-Fix shadowstep etc to work more reliably (a minimum distance of your level for shadowstep and making it port up and around objects would help, yonder having minimum distance of twice your level, for example). <br>
-Add in an escape gate spell that lets Wizards gate at 2-3 seconds for more mana than regular gate (150 mana, for example). Why wouldn't the masters of teleportation have this? <br>
-Add in an upgrade to Resistant Skin. <br>
-Add in an actual Magic Resistance self buff (why was this left out? Enchanters get BOTH the skin spell and the MR buff line for others)<br>
<br>
TELEPORTATION<br>
-Add personal gate to South Ro as well as a group gate. <br>
-Move WK porter to other side of zone.  Yes, the abscond puts you there now but really... this is just obvious.<br>
-Add in a fade-type spell that teleports a random (minimum 3xlevel) distance but within 90 degrees of facing either direction (in other words, you go forward, slightly left or right randomly but FORWARD). <br>
-Make Translocates (push ports) require the TARGET have a portal chip that is consumed, not the Wizard. Or just drop the silly portal chip idea entirely.<br>
 <br>
SEEKING KNOWLEDGE <br>
This is an area that Verant just jettisoned, which truly is sad. It can be worked on without giving Wizards ANY more power, but more use to groups and more rounded design. <br>
-fix Bind Sight to work like it used to (can target monsters not in your LOS). <br>
-Add in a swimming Eye of Zomm that can move through water at, say, 100 swim level, or simply make Eye of Zomm swim.<br>
-Lower Chill Sight to level 24 and Heat Sight to level 8. <br>
-Add in a spell that eliminates environmental clutter for Wizards (no snow, fog, etc) at level 29.<br>
-Add in a spell that makes water, blood, etc clear to see through at level 16. <br>
<br>
THE PAYBACK<br>
To get all these goodies and changes you have to give a little, and here's where I would do it: <br>
-Eliminate bonds of force and atols spirit shackles.<br>
-Eliminate planar gates and give to Clerics or make walk on only.<br>
-Eliminate Invis to Undead (why do we have this anyway? Clerics would feel better if we had it taken and it really doesn't fit the class).<br>
-Eliminate bolts (we'd have the range anyway and it would give Magicians something extra special looking and interesting unique to their class).<br>
-Eliminate all magnify/glimpse/gaze etc spells (they don't work anyway). If not this, then have THESE spells increase spell range while in use.<br>
<br>
This gives us a superior grouping class with poorer soloing ability, unique utility, and greater and more obvious level of superiority in attack power without being overpowering.  It would give Wizards more tools in combat at the cost of a few abilities.  Now if Verant took its &quot;similar ability in all areas&quot; doctrine to other classes besides Priest Classes (you note they only mean POST 55, their new break point of where they care about) then the snare wouldn't have to be removed and we wouldn't be significantly better at soloing if at all. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 8/30/02 12:19:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzefirstormwatch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zefir stormwatch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/4/02 4:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> I will submit that I dont believe increasing our damage output (as suggested) will balance Wizards, nor make us more desireable in groups. I do think it will help, but I also think there will need to be more done outside of Nuking abilites.<br>
<br>
It's far too difficult to compete with a Monk or Rogue (as someone referenced as our real competition), who doesnt have to med, in damage. The small increases suggested wont relieve this much at all. And I dont think these changes would distance Wizards enough from the other caster classes we'd compete with to make a difference either.<br>
<br>
As much as some people admire Wizards for the 'illusion' of our great nuking abilites, we arent taken into groups for those reasons. Post 50, most groups have taken my Wizard into a group for one of 3 reasons exclusive of my dmg abilities: snare, evac (TLs with this also), and as one more person to do dmg.<br>
<br>
In situations that can be managed without Evac, or already having a snarer (druid/ranger/etc), then a rogue or other high dmg melee class or more rounded caster class will be taken. A less expensive nuke or faster mana regen abilities, unless very very significant, doesnt help much against a rogue that doesnt ever have to med.<br>
<br>
So ... the small advances ask for just wont help much. Being too focused as a caster in one area isnt helpful considering the downside of mana recovery. And asking to remove certain abilites (Atol's) will cause us more dmg than good. Making us more rounded, perhaps in new areas, would help us, make us more desired.<br>
<br>
Zefir Stormwatch<br>
